examples.jmdp

Class OrderProcessing

  • java.lang.Object
    • jmarkov.jmdp.MDP<S,A>
      • jmarkov.jmdp.InfiniteMDP<S,A>

          • examples.jmdp.OrderProcessing

  • public class OrderProcessing
extends DTMDP<examples.jmdp.PendingOrders,examples.jmdp.ProcessAction>
    A company receives orders at a random rate. At each stage, the company can decide whether to process no orders incurring in a cost of unfilled order per order per stage, or to process all the pending orders incurring in a setup cost. This class belongs to the examples supplied in the package jmdp. The objective of this file is to show as clear as possible a simple way to use the jmdp package as a tool for solving problems. The complete details of the present problems are explained in the documentation. See Bersekas, "Dynamic Programming and Control".
    Author:
    Andres Sarmiento and Germán Riaño - Universidad de Los Andes
